      "type": "html",
      "id": "65498986f6e51ce2",
      "text": "\"Latchem (2005) notes how many of the research papers and conference presentations on edu- cational technology reflect well upon the institutions, providers and programmes and ignore or play down the failures. A research culture of <strong>“never admit to failure and never admit to being proved wrong”</strong> is completely at variance withwhat is required to transformeducational technol- ogy into successful evidence-based policy and practice.\" (p. 8) "
