    },
    {
      "type": "html",
      "id": "4a6d545d62c43d5b",
      "text": "\"Some researchers have attempted to identify particular student characteristics or other factors that can be used to predict whether a student might drop out of, or otherwise fail to achieve satisfactory results in an e- learning course (Bouhnik & Marcus, 2006). Characteristics and other circumstances identified in previous studies, including clarity of design, interaction with instructors, and active discussion in the context of the course (Swan, 2001), will enhance students’ satisfaction toward e-learning.\" (p. 265)"
